    },
    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "sn51.77-86:1.1",
          "pli": "“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, uddhambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni. ",
          "en": "“Mendicants, there are five higher fetters. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn51.77-86:1.2",
          "pli": "Katamāni pañca? ",
          "en": "What five? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn51.77-86:1.3",
          "pli": "Rūparāgo, arūparāgo, māno, uddhaccaṃ, avijjā—",
          "en": "Desire for rebirth in the realm of luminous form, desire for rebirth in the formless realm, conceit, restlessness, and ignorance. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn51.77-86:1.4",
          "pli": "imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañcuddhambhāgiyāni saṃyojanāni. ",
          "en": "These are the five higher fetters. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn51.77-86:1.5",
          "pli": "Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ uddhambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ abhiññāya pariññāya parikkhayāya pahānāya cattāro iddhipādā bhāvetabbā. ",
          "en": "The four bases of psychic power should be developed for the direct knowledge, complete understanding, finishing, and giving up of these five higher fetters. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn51.77-86:1.6",
          "pli": "Katame cattāro? ",
          "en": "What four? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn51.77-86:1.7",
          "pli": "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu chandasamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti, ",
          "en": "It’s when a mendicant develops the basis of psychic power that has immersion due to enthusiasm … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn51.77-86:1.8",
          "pli": "vīriyasamādhi … pe … ",
          "en": "energy … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn51.77-86:1.9",
          "pli": "cittasamādhi … ",
          "en": "mental development … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn51.77-86:1.10",
          "pli": "vīmaṃsāsamādhippadhānasaṅkhārasamannāgataṃ iddhipādaṃ bhāveti. ",
          "en": "inquiry, and active effort. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn51.77-86:1.11",
          "pli": "Imesaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ uddhambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ abhiññāya pariññāya parikkhayāya pahānāya ime cattāro iddhipādā bhāvetabbā”ti. ",
          "en": "These four bases of psychic power should be developed for the direct knowledge, complete understanding, finishing, and giving up of these five higher fetters.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn51.77-86:1.12",
          "pli": "(Yathā maggasaṃyuttaṃ tathā vitthāretabbaṃ.) ",
          "en": "(To be expanded as in the Linked Discourses on the Path at SN 45.171–180.) "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn51.77-86:1.13",
          "pli": "Oghavaggo aṭṭhamo. ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn51.77-86:2.1",
          "pli": "Ogho yogo upādānaṃ, ",
          "en": "Floods, bonds, grasping, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn51.77-86:2.2",
          "pli": "ganthā anusayena ca; ",
          "en": "ties, and underlying tendencies, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn51.77-86:2.3",
          "pli": "Kāmaguṇā nīvaraṇā, ",
          "en": "kinds of sensual stimulation, hindrances, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn51.77-86:2.4",
          "pli": "khandhā oruddhambhāgiyāti. ",
          "en": "aggregates, and fetters high and low. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn51.77-86:2.5",
          "pli": "Iddhipādasaṃyuttaṃ sattamaṃ. ",
          "en": "The Linked Discourses on the Bases of psychic Power is the seventh section."
        }
      ],
